article.description: Alabama State beats Fort Valley State 76-65
article.headline: Alabama State beats Fort Valley State 76-65
article.linkText: Alabama State beats Fort Valley State 76-65
article.story: MONTGOMERY, Ala. -- Bobby Brown scored 16 points, Wendell Lewis added 13, and Alabama State beat Division II Fort Valley State 76-65 on Tuesday. Luther Page scored 11 points, Maurice Strong grabbed 10 rebounds, and Jamel Waters had five steals and five assists for the Hornets (4-5). Brown opened with a 3-pointer and Alabama State led 12-7, then used a 9-2 run to pull away. Derrick Spear hit back-to-back 3-pointers for Fort Valley State, but the Wildcats trailed 41-30 at halftime. Both Brown and Wendell Lewis scored eight points in the half and the Hornets outshot the Wildcats 51.7 percent to 39.3 percent. The teams traded baskets in the second half and the Hornets stayed ahead. Brown hit consecutive 3s for a 52-34 Alabama State lead, then Lewis mad a layup for a 73-62 lead with 2:34 left. Spear led the Wildcats (0-8) with 18, Ralph Wilson had 15 and Tyrone Brinson 12.
